80
00:04:41.940 --> 00:04:44.300
subtypes and calls the group

81
00:04:45.320 --> 00:04:48.820
non-GCB that is classified using the Hans

82
00:04:48.900 --> 00:04:52.880
algorithm here because it has about 20%

83
00:04:52.940 --> 00:04:56.900
misclassification of lymphomas in the modern era

84
00:04:56.920 --> 00:05:00.810
when that's used. And I'll return to that throughout the talk about how

85
00:05:01.220 --> 00:05:05.080
we are currently classifying lymphomas really does not translate into ways

86
00:05:05.300 --> 00:05:08.020
that we can make actionable clinically at this point.

87
00:05:09.140 --> 00:05:13.060
And what we've seen over a series of years

88
00:05:13.160 --> 00:05:17.100
after that first trial that I showed you of R-CHOP versus CHOP were

89
00:05:17.300 --> 00:05:21.180
a few other trials that also showed that adding rituximab to

90
00:05:21.220 --> 00:05:25.020
therapy provided benefits. But then with a series of trials after

91
00:05:25.080 --> 00:05:28.980
that, there were a number of modifications with a focus on being able to

92
00:05:29.380 --> 00:05:32.890
address that molecular classification, predominantly using the Hans algorithm,

93
00:05:33.320 --> 00:05:37.260
that really were ultimately negative trials, with the only positive one of

94
00:05:37.300 --> 00:05:41.070
