111
00:06:38.472 --> 00:06:42.332
classifications with newer technologies like detection of minimum

112
00:06:42.412 --> 00:06:43.722
residual disease and others,

113
00:06:44.662 --> 00:06:48.272
that we now need to go back and recreate new endpoints,

114
00:06:48.372 --> 00:06:52.332
because even with progression-free survival we would likely expect that it

115
00:06:52.352 --> 00:06:56.072
will take seven to 10 years for a new drug to reach that

116
00:06:56.392 --> 00:06:59.832
endpoint, which is unacceptably long for patients to

117
00:06:59.872 --> 00:07:03.352
wait for new therapies for the frontline for diffuse large B-cell lymphoma.

118
00:07:04.432 --> 00:07:08.392
But while this therapy was available, or while this endpoint

119
00:07:08.452 --> 00:07:11.892
was available, we ultimately were able to use that

120
00:07:12.312 --> 00:07:16.012
for the development and validation of a

121
00:07:16.152 --> 00:07:19.922
new therapy for patients with diffuse large B-cell lymphoma and some of

122
00:07:20.072 --> 00:07:23.532
the folks in the room with me were key players in

123
00:07:23.592 --> 00:07:27.372
that. I was the US lead for this clinical trial.

124
00:07:28.052 --> 00:07:31.352
That was a worldwide clinical trial that involved the new

125
00:07:31.652 --> 00:07:34.852
anti-CD79B antibody drug conjugate

