131
00:07:54.362 --> 00:07:57.572
And this was for patients stratified by International

132
00:07:57.652 --> 00:08:01.352
Prognostic Index who had a higher IPI score.

133
00:08:02.392 --> 00:08:06.332
And as you can see here, progression-free survival, that endpoint

134
00:08:06.341 --> 00:08:10.242
that we developed through surrogacy was used as the endpoint for this trial.

135
00:08:10.792 --> 00:08:14.032
And ultimately what that trial showed was an improvement in progression-free

136
00:08:14.052 --> 00:08:17.631
survival for the arm shown here in green that received polo R-CHIP

137
00:08:17.952 --> 00:08:21.232
compared to patients who received R-CHOP with a hazard ratio of

138
00:08:21.272 --> 00:08:22.832
0.73, and I'll have you

139
00:08:23.812 --> 00:08:26.232
remember and focus on that hazard ratio.

140
00:08:27.212 --> 00:08:30.732
But that provides a meaningful benefit for patients with

141
00:08:30.972 --> 00:08:34.672
diffuse large B-cell lymphoma when selected by International

142
00:08:34.752 --> 00:08:36.192
Prognostic Index

143
00:08:37.432 --> 00:08:38.512
for patients overall.

144
00:08:39.972 --> 00:08:43.712
And what we've seen more recently in a follow-up to this trial that was published

145
00:08:43.752 --> 00:08:47.362
