206
00:12:28.932 --> 00:12:32.896
differently.I think the other thing that is just

207
00:12:33.196 --> 00:12:36.936
new and hot off the presses and came out earlier this week is a follow-up

208
00:12:37.276 --> 00:12:41.196
to this work that was led by Laura Hilton, who's

209
00:12:41.216 --> 00:12:45.056
a collaborator of ours from British Columbia, who showed that

210
00:12:45.116 --> 00:12:48.476
if you look using the newer

211
00:12:48.536 --> 00:12:52.056
classification system in terms of the molecular classifiers

212
00:12:52.696 --> 00:12:56.416
for the group that had EZB, ST2,

